 MetLife provides the best value. It has been in service since the 1860s and has excellent scores from the top independent raters, making it a safe bet that the company will outlive you to pay your beneficiaries. Further, MetLife has dedicated specialists to help your beneficiaries with the claims process and managing the payout, as well as with handling paperwork associated with government benefits and with finding grief counseling. These facts, along with the many other life insurance options and supplemental services, makes MetLife the top choice for life insurance."]},"id":"312e70f8-6e4e-40be-b299-709b7cfa7e6b","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Plan Options"},"id":"aac73647-a412-4bc1-9d5e-d62d10e3773f","type":"heading"},{"data":{"path":"/jnVjegeGMGiGavdKfxdZoF.jpg","link":{"href":"","rel":null,"target":""},"caption":"MetLife is the only life insurance company we reviewed that had a term life insurance plan that lasted up to age 90 rather than a specific number of years. The simplified term plan does not require an exam, but it only asks two health questions. You can get it for up to $100,000 in coverage. If you need more, there&#39;s level term insurance. It requires an exam, but you can purchase as much coverage as you need. Finally, a one-year term plan can provide a good stopgap, such as if you are between jobs, and can be converted if you purchase a rider with the plan.","fullscreen":true,"importSrc":"http://www.toptenreviews.com/i/rev/scrn/small/3495-metlife3.jpg","src":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/jnVjegeGMGiGavdKfxdZoF.jpg","credit":"","align":"","id":"jnVjegeGMGiGavdKfxdZoF","mos":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/jnVjegeGMGiGavdKfxdZoF.jpg","alt":""},"id":"fd5ca4ea-792c-470a-8835-2bb1bf05b37d","type":"image"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Whole life plans also come with the option of no medical exam. Of course, you pay higher premiums for this. These plans last your lifetime and have cash value. Universal life offers flexibility of payments and returns, 